<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="350" pageId="4" pageNumber="349" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1127,1152,1591]" pageId="4" pageNumber="349">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,281,1152,1175]" pageId="4" pageNumber="349">Comments.</emphasis>
We studied several species of these two genera and found that their diagnostic features were the same: antennae, wing venation, body structure and ovipositor shape were all identical. The only differences appear to be those suggested by 
<bibRefCitation author="NOYES J. S. &amp; HAYAT M." box="[871,1127,1216,1239]" pageId="4" pageNumber="349" pagination="131 - 395" refId="ref31394" refString="NOYES J. S. &amp; HAYAT M. 1984: A review of the genera of Indo-Pacific Encyrtidae (Hymenoptera: Chalcidoidea). Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History) (Entomology) 48: 131 - 395." type="journal article" year="1984">NOYES &amp; HAYAT (1984)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="NOYES J. S." box="[197,349,1248,1271]" pageId="4" pageNumber="349" pagination="133 - 166" refId="ref31237" refString="NOYES J. S. 1990: Chapter 2.4. 2. Encyrtidae. Pp. 133 - 166. In: ROZEN D. (ed.): The Armored Scale Insects. Their Biology, Natural Enemies and Control. World Crop Pests 4 B. Elsevier, Amsterdam, London, New York and Tokyo, 668 pp." type="book chapter" year="1990">NOYES (1990)</bibRefCitation>
. In 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Girault" authorityYear="1915" box="[388,555,1248,1271]" class="Insecta" family="Encyrtidae" genus="Epitetracnemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="349" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[388,555,1248,1271]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="349">Epitetracnemus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
there is a line of silvery setae across the face and the fore wing has a stronger pattern of infuscation. In 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ashmead" authorityYear="1900" box="[694,833,1280,1303]" class="Insecta" family="Encyrtidae" genus="Adelencyrtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="349" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[694,833,1280,1303]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="349">Adelencyrtus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the face lacks a line of silvery setae and the fore wing is generally hyaline or only weakly infuscate. However these characters show some varaibility across these genera. 
<bibRefCitation author="ZHANG Y. - Z. &amp; SHI Z. - Y." box="[733,958,1344,1367]" pageId="4" pageNumber="349" pagination="1 - 26" refId="ref33663" refString="ZHANG Y. - Z. &amp; SHI Z. - Y. 2010: The species of Adelencyrtus Ashmead and Epitetracnemus Girault (Hymenoptera: Encyrtidae) from China. Zootaxa 2605: 1 - 26." type="journal article" year="2010">ZHANG &amp; SHI (2010)</bibRefCitation>
also stated that these two genera are very close and that further studies were needed to assess the validity of the two genera. For instance 
<taxonomicName authority="Noyes &amp; Ren, 1987" authorityName="Noyes &amp; Ren" authorityYear="1987" box="[454,903,1408,1431]" class="Insecta" family="Encyrtidae" genus="Epitetracnemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="349" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="comis">
<emphasis box="[454,689,1408,1431]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="349">Epitetracnemus comis</emphasis>
Noyes &amp; Ren, 1987
</taxonomicName>
is extremely close to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ashmead" authorityYear="1900" box="[151,289,1440,1463]" class="Insecta" family="Encyrtidae" genus="Adelencyrtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="349" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,289,1440,1463]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="349">Adelencyrtus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and would run to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ashmead" authorityYear="1900" box="[474,612,1440,1463]" class="Insecta" family="Encyrtidae" genus="Adelencyrtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="349" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[474,612,1440,1463]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="349">Adelencyrtus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in TRJAPITZINâ€™ s (1989) key to Palaearctic species. In this species, the line of silver setae across the face is hardly present and therefore we suggest that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Girault" authorityYear="1915" box="[199,366,1504,1527]" class="Insecta" family="Encyrtidae" genus="Epitetracnemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="349" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[199,366,1504,1527]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="349">Epitetracnemus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be treated as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ashmead" authorityYear="1900" box="[826,965,1504,1527]" class="Insecta" family="Encyrtidae" genus="Adelencyrtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="349" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[826,965,1504,1527]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="349">Adelencyrtus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. As a result of this synonymy, besides the combinations proposed below, the following new combinations are proposed: 
<taxonomicName authority="(Zhang &amp; Shi, 2010)" authorityName="Japoshvili &amp; Higashiura &amp; Kamitani" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Zhang &amp; Shi" baseAuthorityYear="2010" box="[300,745,1568,1591]" class="Insecta" family="Encyrtidae" genus="Adelencyrtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="349" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bandus" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[300,521,1568,1591]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="349">Adelencyrtus bandus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="ZHANG Y. - Z. &amp; SHI Z. - Y." box="[534,738,1568,1591]" pageId="4" pageNumber="349" pagination="1 - 26" refId="ref33663" refString="ZHANG Y. - Z. &amp; SHI Z. - Y. 2010: The species of Adelencyrtus Ashmead and Epitetracnemus Girault (Hymenoptera: Encyrtidae) from China. Zootaxa 2605: 1 - 26." type="journal article" year="2010">Zhang &amp; Shi, 2010</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[751,872,1568,1591]" pageId="4" pageNumber="349">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[751,872,1568,1591]" pageId="4" pageNumber="349" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Girault" authorityYear="1915" box="[943,1110,1568,1591]" class="Insecta" family="Encyrtidae" genus="Epitetracnemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="349" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[943,1110,1568,1591]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="349">Epitetracnemus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
),
</paragraph>
